62 The affidavit may be filed any time after a medical professional determines the existence
63 of a detectable human heartbeat that prevents the woman from terminating the pregnancy
64 and before the birth of the child. The Department of Human Services shall process any
65 claims for compensation pursuant to this chapter in a timely manner.
66 (2) Upon receipt of an affidavit filed by a woman pursuant to this subsection, the
67 Department of Human Services shall assign a case manager to the woman in order to
68 develop a case plan to ensure that the woman is receiving adequate prenatal care, and to
69 determine any available state funded programs and services for which the woman and
70 embryo or fetus are eligible. The case manager shall meet with the pregnant woman
71 monthly in person to ensure that the pregnancy is continuing and that the requisite
72 programs, services, and funding are accessible. As part of the prenatal visits, the case
73 manager shall review all reports of the nurse assigned to the pregnant woman to ensure
74 that the woman is maintaining a nutritious, healthy lifestyle for development of the
75 embryo or fetus. After the birth of the child, the case manager shall make a reasonable
76 number of face-to-face visits, as determined by Department of Human Services
77 regulation, to ensure that the requisite programs, services, and funding continue to be
78 accessible for the woman and her child.
79 (b) The General Assembly shall establish a fund, separate and apart from the general fund,
80 to which shall be annually appropriated sufficient funds to award the compensation
81 authorized and required pursuant to this chapter and to fund the operational costs incurred
82 by the Department of Human Services in fulfilling the duties outlined in subsection (a) of
83 this Code section."
84 SECTION 3.
85 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
